parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation and blowout can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Treadle Valve Causing Rear Wheel Brake Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty treadle valve can cause the rear wheel brakes to overheat and drag, leading to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: unusual noise or vibrations when braking

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Drum Rubbing Causing Squealing Noise
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rubbing of the brake drums can cause the brakes to squeal, which can be a sign of worn or faulty brake components, leading to reduced braking performance and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Squealing or grinding noise when applying the brakes
vibration or pulsation in the brake pedal

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The uneven weight distribution between the front and rear axles can cause the vehicle to gallop or bounce severely when driving over expansion joints, potentially leading to loss of control, accidents, or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The vehicle gallops or bounces severely when driving over expansion joints
the front tires may leave the ground
and the vehicle may be difficult to handle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the engine to shut down, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded. In this case, the failure also caused the brakes and steering to fail, further increasing the risk of accidents.
The failure of the electrical system can cause multiple systems to fail, including the fuel pump, brakes, and steering, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
The failure of the air conditioning clutch assembly can cause the air conditioning system to malfunction, leading to reduced cooling performance, increased engine load, and potential overheating.
symptoms: The air conditioning system fails to cool
the air conditioning compressor clutch does not engage
the air conditioning compressor clutch is noisy or vibrates excessively
the air conditioning system blows warm air.
